figure_1.title: Figure 1.
figure_1.caption:
Consort Diagram
Note. Low/Low=low cognitive-low interpersonal; High Cog/Low Int=high cognitive-low interpersonal; Low Cog/High Int=low cognitive-high interpersonal; High/High=high cognitive-high interpersonal

figure_2.title: Figure 2.
figure_2.caption:
Moderation Effects During 18-Month Follow-up.
Notes. CDI = depressive symptoms. CBQF = conflict with father; CRSQ = rumination; HSC = hopelessness. The y-axis represents change in depression scores from post-intervention through 18-month follow-up. On the x-axis, high and low correspond to one standard deviation above or below the mean of each moderator.
